<br>
Necromancer: <br>
Funeral Pyre is 240 a tick for 9 ticks with a ratio of 4.8 <br>
Pyrocuor is 111 a tick for 18 ticks with a ratio of 5.0 <br>
Cessation of Cor is 100 a tick for 10 ticks with a ratio of 4.0 <br>
<br>
So- 451(DPS of 75) a tick multiplied by 10 ticks is 4510 damage over a minute, mutiply this by a 10 minute fight (typical VT fight atm) that's 45100 damage per necro, give or take focus effect items. <br>
<br>
I think this is a great thing for casters, especially necros, who for now more than one on a raid are basically useless, unless your necros are like my guilds and like the chain ignite bones a mob( which by the way is really funny when they do that to a large mob when it does a fake gate). Not to mention the fact that druids, shamans and even bards can cast dots. I know that they are doing away with the 15 buff slot limit on npc's but I do hope they keep in within reason, maybe 25 or 30.<br>
